<P><B>Organizational offerings (NY Times, 13 Feb)</B>
<BR>&nbsp;
<BLOCKQUOTE><B>Ford Offering each of its 350,000 employees</B>

<P><B>A computer, printer, and unlimited access</B>

<P><B>for $5 per month</B>

<P><B>Delta, 80,000 employees, similar,</B>

<P><B>but not quite as generous</B></BLOCKQUOTE>


<P><B>&nbsp;</B> --------------------------------------------------

<P><B>Why is Ford doing this?</B>
<BR>&nbsp;
<BLOCKQUOTE><B>Increasing computer literacy</B>

<P><B>Some concern that Ford will use it</B>

<P><B>for other reasons, e.g.,</B>

<P><B>disseminate information to employees</B>

<P><B>get people to work from home</B>

<P><B>stifle anti-Ford messages</B>
<BR>&nbsp;</BLOCKQUOTE>
<B>Free (or almost free) PC's</B>
<BR>&nbsp;
<BLOCKQUOTE><B>for signing up for internet service</B>

<P><B>for providing information</B>
